{:component/id :orbiplex/local-relationship-layer
 :component/title "Local Relationship Layer"
 :component/type :host-owned-substrate
 :component/status :partial

 :summary
 "Solution-level host-owned substrate for the user's private relationship
 state: relationship classes, append-only membership facts, pairwise nym
 continuity, and relationship-derived policy predicates. Canonical state
 lives in the Pseudonym Vault; SQLite projection is rebuildable cache.
 Replaces partial models in Messaging, Artifact Delivery, and Contact
 Catalog."

 :must-implement
 [{:cap/id :relationship-schema-set
   :title "Relationship Schema Set"
   :kind :contract
   :based-on ["doc/project/40-proposals/065-local-relationship-layer.md"]
   :schemas ["relationship-class.v1"
             "relationship-class-changed.v1"
             "relationship-membership-fact.v1"
             "pairwise-nym-binding-fact.v1"
             "pairwise-nym-binding.v1"]
   :responsibilities
   ["Separate class definition (mutable projection) from class change facts (append-only)"
    "Express membership transitions as append-only facts with owner/ref, status, actor/ref, supersedes/fact-id as projection hint"
    "Split pairwise nym binding into append-only fact stream and sealed projection"
    "Reserve well-known class IDs `contacts` and `friends`; require namespace for all other classes"
    "Treat `blocked` as a status on memberships, never a class equivalent to `contacts`/`friends`"]
   :status :done}

  {:cap/id :relationship-policy-predicate-schema-set
   :title "Relationship Policy Predicate Schema Set"
   :kind :contract
   :based-on ["doc/project/40-proposals/065-local-relationship-layer.md"]
   :schemas ["relationship-policy-predicate.v1"
             "relationship-policy-candidate.v1"
             "relationship-policy-decision.v1"]
   :responsibilities
   ["Express middleware/operator-declared trust conditions as predicates with mandatory effect/scope"
    "Express host-internal eligibility input as candidates with candidate/effects (never `allowed/effects`)"
    "Express host-bound outcomes as decisions returned to middleware with redacted evidence refs"
    "Enforce three-tier separation: predicate = condition, candidate = input, decision = bound outcome"]
   :status :done}

  {:cap/id :vault-backed-canonical-truth
   :title "Vault-Backed Canonical Truth"
   :kind :storage-contract
   :based-on ["doc/project/60-solutions/026-pseudonym-vault-and-key-roles/026-pseudonym-vault-and-key-roles.md"
              "doc/project/40-proposals/065-local-relationship-layer.md"]
   :schemas ["pseudonym-vault.v1"]
   :responsibilities
   ["Store sealed event log plus latest sealed snapshot as canonical truth"
    "Treat snapshot alone as checkpoint accelerator, never alternate authority"
    "Extend pseudonym-vault.v1 additively with `local-relationship` inner-entry kind"
    "Preserve unknown inner-entry kinds verbatim on reseal; fail closed on critical=true unknown entries"
    "Recover by replaying sealed event log from last good snapshot"]
   :status :partial
   :notes "Daemon startup now replays Pseudonym Vault `local-relationship` entries and seeds default classes when the vault is writable. The current write path still needs vault-first atomic hardening."}

  {:cap/id :sqlite-projection-with-privacy-boundary
